<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
In the previous versions all classes and races had some combat modifiers, which modified combat success. This means that a paladin with 50 in weaponmastery skill was a better warrior than a alchemist with the same skill. Is it true in 2.3 too? <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: No, the internal class and race modifiers were removed in version 2.3.0, i.e. a warrior, a priest and a mage with a skill of 50.0 are handled similarly. Race and class only determine the starting skill level and the skill modifier. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./VagaBond">VagaBond</a>: In this case I see the idea behind warrior mages. Alchemists became much better this way I guess..  Is there a chance in the future to eliminate or change the traps and monster attacks which make wands empty? These make magic device oriented alchemists too hard to play. Even a new ability (wandwarded) could be a solution. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":-)" height="15" width="15"> It is in the pipeline for ToME 3.0.0 (not coded yet): 
<pre>-- DGDGDGDG *CODE ME*
new_ability
{
        define_as = "AB_STICK_FORTIFICATION"
        name = "Sticks Fortification"
        desc =
        {
                "Allows you to make sticks(wands, staves, rods) resistant to",
                "charges draining attacks.",
                "Prereq: Alchemy@35, INT@25",
        }
        cost = 10
        skills = { Alchemy = 35 }
        stats = { [A_INT] = 25 }
}
</pre>
</p>
<p>
<a href="./VagaBond">VagaBond</a>: yeah <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> And what are the chances of this presented in the 2.3 series? <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Zero.  I've already asked for 2.3.0 to be shipped, and no new game changes will be allowed in the 2.3 series.  Besides, New New Alchemy isn't coming until ToME 3 anyway. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./VagaBond">VagaBond</a>: Good news anyway. Thank you for the information. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: I'm glad you agree it's good news that we're getting 2.3 out the door "before it gets moldy," as I put in my request to ship the thing. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: 2.3 might be shipped soon? YAY! <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/biggrin.png" alt=":D" height="15" width="15"> (balloons, streamers, confetti, that sort of thing....) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: It will be shipped as soon as the illustrious maintainer gets a chance to compile, package, upload, and announce. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./DarkGod">DarkGod</a>: Sadly, the illustrious maintainer was sick last week and without an internet connection this week :/ I should get it back for the next weekend. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./BurbLulls">BurbLulls</a></strong>: Heh, the God of Darkness sick. It doesn't bear thinking about :p  
</p>

